     5→//! - jjx_chalk: Empty commit marking a steeplechase event (pace-level)
     6→//! - Heat-level commits: nominate, slate, rail, tally, draft, retire
     7→//!
     8→//! Commit format: `jjb:BRAND:IDENTITY[:ACTION]: message`
     9→//! - BRAND: Repository identifier (e.g., "RBM")
    10→//! - IDENTITY: ₢CORONET for pace-level, ₣FIREMARK for heat-level
    11→//! - ACTION: Single letter code (optional for standard notch)
    12→//!
    13→//! The actual commit execution is handled by vorc_commit in the vok crate.
    14→//! This module exports formatting functions that the CLI handlers use.
    15→
    16→use crate::jjrf_favor::{Coronet, Firemark, CORONET_PREFIX, FIREMARK_PREFIX};
    17→
    18→/// Default brand identifier (placeholder until configured by installation-identifier pace)
    19→const DEFAULT_BRAND: &str = "RBM";
